The paper deals with optimization of functions using only function evaluations, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The use of simulated annealing and log-concave distributions suggests that the paper is likely to be in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or numerical analysis (cs.NA). The mention of dynamic programming and stochastic programming suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the mention of online learning suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of operations research (cs.OC).
